{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fight of Our Lives: Reform mental health support for veterans",
        "additional_details": "Offer annual mental health check-ups for three years following discharge\r\nCreate a Veterans Mental Health Scheme offering ongoing screening for conditions such as PTSD and a rapid intervention service for Veterans in distress\r\nRequire coroners to record Veterans suicide\r\n \r\nI served 24 years with the Royal Regiment of Fusiliers. In 2020 I have lost friends to the hidden epidemic in the Veterans community \u2013 Suicide.\r\n \r\nAmongst our allies, the UK is one of a few countries that do not record how many veterans die from suicide, hiding the true scale of the problem.\r\n \r\nThis is the Fight of Our Lives.\r\n \r\nVeterans suicide should not be hidden.\r\n \r\nVeteran suicide must be discussed and taken seriously. It could mean the difference between life and death.",
        "background": "We want the Government to:",
